4:
A Halloween concert, eh? Sounds
great! Can I go, too?
7:
Of course. I made sure to reserve a
seat for you.
10:
...All right, maintenance is done, and
she's all good to go now!
13:
Thank you, Midivari. You're always so
helpful.
16:
Not at all. It's always a delight to see
you and Carol.
18:
By the way, do you know what you're
going to play at the concert?
24:
I've been told that I can play any
song and hold the event however I
want, but I'm having trouble
deciding...
27:
Yeah... I get that! It's a rough
business making music for a client
when they give you zero bytes of
direction!
30:
Oh, I wasn't aware that you're a
composer, Midivari.
33:
I'd like to come up with something
fitting for Halloween, but I'm having
trouble choosing songs...
58: Did you sleep enough last night?
62:
Well... I... I was so lost in thought that
the sun was up before I knew it.
65:
I'm... composing a song, you see. For
the Halloween concert.
70:
Really? I didn't know you wrote your
own music.
74: This is my first time, actually.
77:
Midivari encouraged me to make
my own music, since I couldn't
decide what to play.
86:
But... Even with all of Midivari's
advice, I can't seem to come up with
anything that sounds very good...
92:
Perhaps writing music is beyond my
ability...
97:
...Ability aside, is this something you
want to try?
105:
I want to hear Carol play my own
song.
108:
Nothing would make me happier
than creating something that
makes everyone smile...
118:
...Why don't we try talking to
someone in the industry?
126:
...That's the melody I'm thinking of,
but... What do you think?
130:
Th-that's the piece you're having
trouble with? It's really good...
134:
Really?
Don't you think it feels... off,
somehow?
138:
M-maybe? I'm not sure...
C-could I try singing it?
167:
Yes, but... You sang with a bit of a
tighter rhythm, don't you think?
171:
Tighter, huh? Well, it's a pretty calm
song to begin with, so I thought I'd...
179: I... I did it. I'm finished!
182:
U-um... Can we go pay Midivari a
visit?
185:
I want you two, Dia, and Midivari to
be the first to hear it!
189: ...Sure! I bet we're all going to love it.
198:
I hope you enjoy this as much as I
will, Carol...
205:
Wow! I can't believe what she's done
with the song!
209:
It's lovely... Lyra looks like she's
having fun, too.
217:
Carol, I had no idea you could sound
like that...
224:
Th-thank you! I couldn't have done it
without everyone's help!
227:
Perhaps it's selfish of me to say this,
but...
230:
Since I'm allowed to decide who will
perform at the event...
233:
Well, if it's possible... I want to
perform together with Dia!
236:
And... I think there are many in
Starview Village who might want to
perform too, so I'd love to have them
join me as well.
240: Well, um... If it's okay, that is...
245:
Of course it's okay! We'll give them a
show they'll never forget!
250:
There shouldn't be any shortage of
people who'd like to join, too. It'll be
great!
253:
W-wait... Dia and Lyra performing
together? I'm dreaming, right?
Right?!
